PROBLEM 2. Let the set $A=\left\{n \mid n=2^{a} \cdot 3^{b} \cdot 5^{c}\right.$, where $\left.a, b, c \in \mathbb{N}\right\}$.

a) Show that $81 \in A$;

b) Determine the elements of the set $A$ that have exactly 6 divisors.

\section*{Problem 4 - 071034}

We are looking for all triples of natural numbers \(a_{i}(i=1,2,3)\) that satisfy the equation

\[
\sqrt{2 a_{1}^{2}-2 a_{2}^{2}}=a_{3}
\]

and for which \(1 \leq a_{i} \leq 10\) also holds!

3. (50 points) Find the smallest prime $p$ that satisfies $(p, N)=1$, where $N$ is the number of all $\left(a_{0}, a_{1}, \cdots, a_{2012}\right)$ that meet the following conditions:
(1) $\left(a_{0}, a_{1}, \cdots, a_{2012}\right)$ is a permutation of $0,1, \cdots, 2012$;
(2) For any positive divisor $m$ of 2013 and all $n(0 \leqslant n<n+m \leqslant 2012)$, $m \mid\left(a_{n+m}-a_{n}\right)$.
